    117 /**
    118 * Given a resource and a list of ref paths - resolves them all
    119 * @param {Object} obj FHIR Resource
    120 * @param {Object} fhirOptions The fhir options of the initiating request call
    121 * @param {Object} cache A map to store fetched refs
    122 * @param {FhirClient} client The client instance
    123 * @private

    125 function resolveRefs(obj, fhirOptions, cache, client) {
    126
    127 // 1. Sanitize paths, remove any invalid ones
    128 let paths = makeArray(fhirOptions.resolveReferences)
    129 .filter(Boolean) // No false, 0, null, undefined or ""
    130 .map(path => String(path).trim())

    133 // 2. Remove duplicates
    134 134 paths = paths.filter((p, i) => {

    138 2 return false;
    139 }
    140 68 return true;
    141 });
    142
    143 // 3. Early exit if no valid paths are found
    144 134 if (!paths.length) {
    145 72 return Promise.resolve();

    147
    148 // 4. Group the paths by depth so that child refs are looked up
    149 // after their parents!

    152 const len = path.split(".").length;
    153 68 if (!groups[len]) {
    154 64 groups[len] = [];
    155 }
    156 68 groups[len].push(path);
    157 });
    158
    159 // 5. Execute groups sequentially! Paths within same group are
    160 // fetched in parallel!
    161 /**
    162 * @type any
    163 */
    164 62 let task = Promise.resolve();

    166 const group = groups[len];

    168 return resolveRef(obj, path, fhirOptions.graph, cache, client);

    246 /** 117
    247 * Given a resource and a list of ref paths - resolves them all
    248 * @param {Object} obj FHIR Resource
    249 * @param {Object} fhirOptions The fhir options of the initiating request call
    250 * @param {Object} cache A map to store fetched refs
    251 * @param {FhirClient} client The client instance
    252 * @private

    254
    255
    256 function resolveRefs(obj, fhirOptions, cache, client) { 125
    257 // 1. Sanitize paths, remove any invalid ones 127
    258 134 let paths = 128
    259 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 128
    260 (0, 128
    261 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 128
    262
    263 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 128
    264 _lib 128
    265 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 128
    266 . 128
    267 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 128
    268 makeArray) 128
    269 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 128
    270 (fhirOptions.resolveReferences).filter(Boolean) // No false, 0, null, undefined or "" 129
    271 .map(path => String(path).trim()).filter(Boolean); // No space-only strings 131
    272 // 2. Remove duplicates 133
    273
    274 134 paths = paths.filter((p, i) => { 134
    275 let index = paths.indexOf(p, i + 1); 135
    276
    277 70 if (index > -1) { 136
    278 2 debug("Duplicated reference path \"%s\"", p); 137
    279 2 return false; 138
    280 } 139
    281
    282 68 return true; 140
    283 }); // 3. Early exit if no valid paths are found 143
    284
    285 134 if (!paths.length) { 144
    286 72 return Promise.resolve(); 145
    287 } // 4. Group the paths by depth so that child refs are looked up 148
    288 // after their parents! 149
    289
    290
    291 62 const groups = {}; 150

    293 const len = path.split(".").length; 152
    294
    295 68 if (!groups[len]) { 153
    296 64 groups[len] = []; 154
    297 } 155
    298
    299 68 groups[len].push(path); 156
    300 }); // 5. Execute groups sequentially! Paths within same group are 159
    301 // fetched in parallel! 160
    302
    303 /** 161
    304 * @type any
    305 */
    306
    307 62 let task = Promise.resolve(); 164
    308 62 Object.keys(groups).sort().forEach(len => { 165
    309 const group = groups[len]; 166
    310 64 task = task.then(() => Promise.all(group.map(path => { 167
    311 return resolveRef(obj, path, fhirOptions.graph, cache, client); 168
    312 }))); 167
    313 }); 165
    314 62 return task; 171

    201 /** 121
    202 * Walks through an object (or array) and returns the value found at the
    203 * provided path. This function is very simple so it intentionally does not
    204 * support any argument polymorphism, meaning that the path can only be a
    205 * dot-separated string. If the path is invalid returns undefined.

    207 * @param {String} path The path (eg. "a.b.4.c")
    208 * @returns {*} Whatever is found in the path or undefined
    209 */
    210

    214
    215 310 if (!path) { 132
    216 2 return obj; 133

    218
    219 308 return path.split(".").reduce((out, key) => out ? out[key] : undefined, obj); 135
    220 } 139
    221 /** 141

    225 * @param {*} value The value to set
    226 * @returns {Object} The modified object
    227 */
    228
    229
    230 function setPath(obj, path, value) { 148

    233 32 out[key] = value; 152
    234 } else { 153
    235 12 return out ? out[key] : undefined; 154
    236 } 155
    237 }, obj); 149
    238 33 return obj; 159
    239 } 160

    413 function getPatientParam(conformance, resourceType) { 317

    416
    417 14 const meta = resources.find(r => r.type === resourceType); 322
    418 16 if (!meta) throw new Error("Resource not supported"); // Check if any search parameters are available for this resource 326
    419
    420 14 if (!Array.isArray(meta.searchParam)) throw new Error(`No search parameters supported for "${resourceType}" on this FHIR server`); // This is a rare case vut could happen in generic workflows 330
    421
    422 12 if (resourceType == "Patient" && meta.searchParam.find(x => x.name == "_id")) return "_id"; // Now find the first possible parameter name 334
    423
    424 8 let out = 335

    426 _settings 335

    428 . 335
    429 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 335
    430 patientParams 335
    431 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 335
    432 .find(p => meta.searchParam.find(x => x.name == p)); // If there is no match 337
    433
    434
    435 10 if (!out) throw new Error("I don't know what param to use for " + resourceType); 339
    436 6 return out; 341
    437 } 342

    371 * Builds the token request options. Does not make the request, just

    375 {
    376 const { redirectUri, clientSecret, tokenUri, clientId } = state;
    377
    378 9 if (!redirectUri) {
    379 1 throw new Error("Missing state.redirectUri");
    380 }
    381
    382 8 if (!tokenUri) {
    383 1 throw new Error("Missing state.tokenUri");
    384 }
    385
    386 7 if (!clientId) {
    387 1 throw new Error("Missing state.clientId");
    388 }
    389
    390 const requestOptions = {
    391 method: "POST",
    392 headers: { "content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" },
    393 body: `code=${code}&grant_type=authorization_code&redirect_uri=${
    394 encodeURIComponent(redirectUri)}`
    395 };
    396
    397 // For public apps, authentication is not possible (and thus not required),
    398 // since a client with no secret cannot prove its identity when it issues a
    399 // call. (The end-to-end system can still be secure because the client comes
    400 // from a known, https protected endpoint specified and enforced by the
    401 // redirect uri.) For confidential apps, an Authorization header using HTTP
    402 // Basic authentication is required, where the username is the app’s
    403 // client_id and the password is the app’s client_secret (see example).
    404
    if (
    clientSecret) {
    405 requestOptions.headers.Authorization = "Basic " + btoa(
    406 clientId + ":" + clientSecret
    407 );
    408 debug("Using state.clientSecret to construct the authorization header: %s", requestOptions.headers.Authorization);
    409 } else {
    410 6 debug("No clientSecret found in state. Adding the clientId to the POST body");
    411 6 requestOptions.body += `&client_id=${encodeURIComponent(clientId)}`;
    412 }
    413
    414 6 return requestOptions;
    415 }

    435 export async function init(env, options)

    443 2 return completeAuth(env);
    444 }

    447 // instance have already been created in this session and we should try to
    448 // "revive" it.
    449 4 const storage = env.getStorage();
    450 const key = state || await storage.get(SMART_KEY);
    451 4 const cached = await storage.get(key);
    452 4 if (cached) {
    453 return new Client(env, cached);
    454 }
    455
    456 // Otherwise try to launch
    457 return authorize(env, options).then(() => {
    458 // `init` promises a Client but that cannot happen in this case. The
    459 // browser will be redirected (unload the page and be redirected back
    460 // to it later and the same init function will be called again). On
    461 // success, authorize will resolve with the redirect url but we don't
    462 // want to return that from this promise chain because it is not a
    463 // Client instance. At the same time, if authorize fails, we do want to
    464 // pass the error to those waiting for a client instance.
    465 return new Promise(() => { /* leave it pending!!! */ });
    466 });
    467 }

    528 * Builds the token request options. Does not make the request, just

    532
    533 function buildTokenRequest(code, state) { 375
    534 9 const { 376
    535 redirectUri, 376
    536 clientSecret, 376
    537 tokenUri, 376
    538 clientId 376
    539 } = state; 376
    540
    541 9 if (!redirectUri) { 378
    542 1 throw new Error("Missing state.redirectUri"); 379
    543 } 380
    544
    545 8 if (!tokenUri) { 382
    546 1 throw new Error("Missing state.tokenUri"); 383
    547 } 384
    548
    549 7 if (!clientId) { 386
    550 1 throw new Error("Missing state.clientId"); 387
    551 } 388
    552
    553 6 const requestOptions = { 390
    554 method: "POST", 390
    555 headers: { 392
    556 "content-type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" 392
    557 }, 390
    558 body: `code=${code}&grant_type=authorization_code&redirect_uri=${encodeURIComponent(redirectUri)}` 394
    559 }; // For public apps, authentication is not possible (and thus not required), 397
    560 // since a client with no secret cannot prove its identity when it issues a 398
    561 // call. (The end-to-end system can still be secure because the client comes 399
    562 // from a known, https protected endpoint specified and enforced by the 400
    563 // redirect uri.) For confidential apps, an Authorization header using HTTP 401
    564 // Basic authentication is required, where the username is the app’s 402
    565 // client_id and the password is the app’s client_secret (see example). 403
    566
    567
    if (
    clientSecret
    ) {
    		 404
    568 requestOptions.headers.Authorization = "Basic " + 405
    569 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 405
    570 (0, 405
    571 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 405
    572
    573 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 405
    574 _lib 405
    575 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 405
    576 . 405
    577 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 405
    578 btoa) 405
    579 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 405
    580 (clientId + ":" + clientSecret); 405
    581 debug("Using state.clientSecret to construct the authorization header: %s", requestOptions.headers.Authorization); 408
    582 } else { 409
    583 6 debug("No clientSecret found in state. Adding the clientId to the POST body"); 410
    584 6 requestOptions.body += `&client_id=${encodeURIComponent(clientId)}`; 411
    585 } 412
    586
    587 6 return requestOptions; 414
    588 } 415
    589 /** 417

    597 async function ready(env, onSuccess, onError) { 424
    598 2 let task = completeAuth(env); 425
    599
    600
    if (
    onSuccess
    ) {
    		 426
    601 task = task.then(onSuccess); 427
    602 } 428
    603
    604
    if (
    onError
    ) {
    		 429
    605 task = task.catch(onError); 430

    610
    611 async function init(env, options) { 436
    612 6 const url = env.getUrl(); 437
    613 6 const code = url.searchParams.get("code"); 438
    614 6 const state = url.searchParams.get("state"); // if `code` and `state` params are present we need to complete the auth flow 441
    615
    616 6 if (code && state) { 442
    617 2 return completeAuth(env); 443
    618 } // Check for existing client state. If state is found, it means a client 446
    619 // instance have already been created in this session and we should try to 447
    620 // "revive" it. 448
    621
    622
    623 4 const storage = env.getStorage(); 449
    624 4 const key = state || (await storage.get( 450
    625 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 450
    626 _settings 450
    627 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 450
    628 . 450
    629 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 450
    630 SMART_KEY 450
    631 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 450
    632 )); 450
    633 4 const cached = await storage.get(key); 451
    634
    635 4 if (cached) { 452
    636 2 return new 453
    637 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 453
    638 _Client 453
    639 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 453
    640 . 453
    641 /*$lab:coverage:off$*/ 453
    642 default 453
    643 /*$lab:coverage:on$*/ 453
    644 (env, cached); 453
    645 } // Otherwise try to launch 456
    646
    647
    648 2 return authorize(env, options).then(() => { 457
    649 // `init` promises a Client but that cannot happen in this case. The 458
    650 // browser will be redirected (unload the page and be redirected back 459
    651 // to it later and the same init function will be called again). On 460
    652 // success, authorize will resolve with the redirect url but we don't 461
    653 // want to return that from this promise chain because it is not a 462
    654 // Client instance. At the same time, if authorize fails, we do want to 463
    655 // pass the error to those waiting for a client instance. 464
    656 return new Promise(() => { 465
    657 /* leave it pending!!! */ 465
    658 }); 465
    659 }); 457
    660 } 467
